General information:
--------------------------------------------------

xoRET is implemented with XOTcl and Tk. 
xoRET 0.2 requires:
	- XOTcl version 1.6.3 or higher (http://www.xotcl.org)
	- Tk version 8.3 or higher (http://www.tcl.tk)
	- Graphviz version 1.9 or higher (http://www.graphviz.org/)
	- Tcllib version 1.4 or higher (http://tcllib.sourceforge.net/)

Using xoRET:
--------------------------------------------------

Simply unpack the xoRET archive to a local directory (note that the 
xoRET archive unpacks to the "./xoRET-x.y.z" sub-directory when 
unpacked with "tar xvzf xoRET-ver-x.y.z.tar.gz").

To use xoRET:
(0. make sure that all relevant packages and libraries are found in the "auto_path")
1. change to the "xoRET-x.y.z/examples" directory
2. type "wish example01.xotcl" or "wish example02.xotcl"
   (example02 loads a simple and rudimentary example including
    some scenarios, steps, obstacles, etc. -- note that the 
    example is by no means a complete domain model)

Hint: many object-specific (e.g. scenario-specific, role-specific, etc.)
      functions are available via context menus (use right mouse button 
      to access context menus)

